      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder [Player Name],

May this missive find you in able health. I write to you in hopes of striking a bargain with the Court.

By the laws of [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url], I am a purveyor of lies. In my work for the School of Ink and Quill, I have written many texts, and while some of the particulars are at odds with history as taught by those loyal to [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url], I truly believe that our work is not blasphemous, nor treasonous, and does nothing but exemplify the inevitability of [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url].

It is not my place to say what is and isn't worthy of censor, that duty, if I understand correctly, is yours.

My offer is this: If you would preserve my texts, I would submit my neck to any sentence you deem worthy without protest. My life is worth little compared to the texts that required the life's work of countless Sages. I understand such writings will likely need to be kept in a vault far from offending eyes... but if I can be assured our written echoes will live on, my flesh and blood are the Court's to discard.

If you are amenable to my offer, seek me out. My current whereabouts are far from the ruins of the [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url] - see the reverse of this parchment for instructions. If you make your way to the location directed, I will seek you out.

Glory to [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]!

-[url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] L

[On the reverse of this missive is a charcoal sketch of what appears to be a small keep built alongside mountain foothills. A map of the Tiers is drawn in the corner, with a circle that seems to indicate this location is in the Bastard Tier - north and east of the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url].]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
