    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] L,

Your request is a bit unorthodox. If you are aware of your role in creating forbidden lore, surely you must know that asking me to harbor such things is asking me to take your crime upon myself.

But I am not without reason or mercy, and I will at least hear out all that you have to say in person.

-Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Lord or Lady L,

If you were sincere in your desire to surrender to the Court, you are welcome to visit [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url], Archon of Justice, and seek audience with him at the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url]. I assure you, the Archon sleeps very little, and time will be made for a proper hearing.

Beggars cannot be choosers, and the guilty ought not to bargain when their only currency is guilt. Perhaps if you could provide me some more insight to your situation, I'd be less inclined to assume this is some sort of trap.

-Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear '[url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] L,'

One does not haggle with the law. If you are a peddler of falsehood, you will perish, and your written lies will follow.

-Fatebinder [Player Name]
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
